        "subject": "LU-9859 libcfs: discard cfs_trace_allocate_string_buffer()",
        "message": "LU-9859 libcfs: discard cfs_trace_allocate_string_buffer()\n\ncfs_trace_allocate_string_buffer() is a simple wrapper\naround kzalloc() that adds little value.  The code is\nclearer if we perform the test and the allocation\ndirectly where needed.\n\nAlso change the test from '>' to '>=' to ensure we\nnever try to allocate more than 2 pages, as that seems\nto be the intent.\n\nLinux-commit: 61c056f8c89243a3e53ce461374023fd4ce76e9e\n\nSigned-off-by: NeilBrown <neilb@suse.de>\nChange-Id: I98775219d4821779040a066625bb62cea30986e0\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
